{"type":"text","timestamp":1778602687448,"sessionID":"ses_1e33fad9fffeLGycJjlvk3M3DA","part":{"id":"prt_e1cf7045e0016iGtC8wLboDlqq","messageID":"msg_e1cf6e28c001aWWASSLQzhcUkR","sessionID":"ses_1e33fad9fffeLGycJjlvk3M3DA","type":"text","text":"---\n### Design Pattern Analysis\nFor the 8 new terms, the `anatomyPartOfAnatomy` pattern is most appropriate. These terms describe specific regions of existing anatomical layers.\n\n**Parent Terms:**\n- For epithelium terms: `UBERON:0005048` (mucosa of fallopian tube)\n- For muscularis terms: `UBERON:0006642` (muscle layer of oviduct)\n\n**Proposed Logical Axioms:**\n- `intersection_of: <Parent Layer> ! <Parent Layer>` (Actually, they should be `is_a` their parent layer)\n- `intersection_of: part_of <Parent Layer> ! <Parent Layer>`\n\nWait, if they are *regions* of the layer, they are part of it.\n\n**Detailed Mapping:**\n\n| Term | `is_a` | `part_of` |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| mesosalpinx epithelium | `UBERON:0005048` | `UBERON:0005048` |\n| antimesosalpinx epithelium | `UBERON:0005048` | `UBERON:0005048` |\n| superior epithelium | `UBERON:0005048` | `UBERON:0005048` |\n| inferior epithelium | `UBERON:00005048` | `UBERON:0005048` |\n| mesosalpinx muscularis | `UBERON:0006642` | `UBERON:0006642` |\n| antimesosalpinx muscularis | `UBERON:0006642` | `UBERON:0006642` |\n| superior muscularis | `UBERON:0006642` | `UBERON:0006642` |\n| inferior muscularis | `UBERON:0006642` | `UBERON:0006642` |\n\n**Definitions:**\nFollowing the genus-differentia form:\n- Mesosalpinx epithelium: \"The portion of the mucosal epithelium of the fallopian tube located on the side of the tube where the mesosalpinx attaches.\"\n- ... (and others follow similar pattern).\n\n**Metadata:**\n- `dc-contributor`: `https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833` (Ellen Quardokus)\n- `term_tracker_item`: `UBERON-3414` (based on issue number)\n\nSince I have the definitions and parent IDs, I can proceed to create the terms. I'll use `obo-checkout.pl` for each or batch them.\n\nI'll start by creating the terms. I'll use new IDs in the range `UBERON:99xxxxx`.\n\nWait, I should double check if any of these names are already used. I already searched for `antimesosalpinx` and found `UBERON:8600117`.\n\nI'll use the following IDs (I will be careful not to guess, but usually I can use a batch):\nActually, the instructions say \"New terms start UBERON:99xxxxx\".\n\nLet's create them.","time":{"start":1778602411102,"end":1778602687447}}}
