{"type":"text","timestamp":1778603872562,"sessionID":"ses_1e33fad9fffeLGycJjlvk3M3DA","part":{"id":"prt_e1d0c99e9001gh5BatulluauVK","messageID":"msg_e1d0c7233001Cp6LOeZm22BtbO","sessionID":"ses_1e33fad9fffeLGycJjlvk3M3DA","type":"text","text":"I have completed the task of addressing issue #3414.\n\n1.  **Research**: Conducted research on the polarity of the fallopian tube, identifying the relationship between mesosalpinx/superior and antimesosalpinx/inferior regions.\n2.  **Implementation**: Created 8 new terms:\n    *   `mesosalpinx epithelium` (UBERON:9900001)\n    *   `antimesosalpinx epithelium` (UBERON:9900002)\n    *   `superior epithelium` (UBERON:9900003)\n    *   `inferior epithelium` (UBERON:9900004)\n    *   `mesosalpinx muscularis` (UBERON:9900005)\n    *   `antimesosalpinx muscularis` (UBERON:9900006)\n    *   `superior muscularis` (UBERON:9900007)\n    *   `inferior muscularis` (UBERON:9900008)\n3.  **Ontology Integration**:\n    *   Assigned parents: `UBERON:0005048` (mucosa) and `UBERON:0006642` (muscle layer).\n    *   Followed the `anatomyPartOfAnatomy` design pattern.\n    *   Added necessary metadata, including contributor ORCID and issue tracker reference.\n    *   Reserialized the ontology using `robot convert`.\n4.  **Finalization**: Committed changes locally and created `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md` and `PR_COMMENTS.md`.","time":{"start":1778603825641,"end":1778603872559}}}
